The R groups of each amino acid remain and
in all condensation reactions, and a new bond is formed between the two
amino acids, called a peptide bond. A dipeptide is a molecule consisting
of two amino acids linked by a peptide bond. A polypeptide is a molecule
consisting of many amino acids linked by peptide bonds.
Polypeptides can contain any number of amino acids, though chains
of fewer than 20 amino acids are usually referred to as oligopeptides
rather than polypeptides. Insulin is a small protein that contains two
polypeptides, one with 21 amino acids and the other with 30. The largest
polypeptide discovered so far is titin, which is part of the structure of
muscle. In humans titin is a chain of 34,350 amino acids, but in mice it is
There are twenty dierent amino acids in polypeptides
The amino acids that are linked together by ribosomes to make
polypeptides all have some identical structural features: a carbon atom
in the centre of the molecule is bonded to an amine group, a carboxyl
group and a hydrogen atom. The carbon atom is also bonded to an R
group, which is different in each amino acid.
